HEADWORD: Potion
<hw>Po"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>potio</ets>,
from <ets>potare</ets> to drink: cf. F. <ets>potion</ets>. See
<er>Poison</er>.]</ety> <def>A draught; a dose; usually, a draught or
dose of a liquid medicine.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Potion</ent>⟦br⟧

